      <section eId="sec_CCRP-914">
        <num>CCRP 914</num>
        <heading>Section </heading>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-914__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>A motion for an appeal may be made orally in open court or by filing a written motion with the clerk. Â The motion shall be entered in the minutes of the court.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-914__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>The motion for an appeal must be made no later than:</p>
          </content>
          <paragraph eId="CCRP-914__subsec_B__subsec_1">
            <num>(1)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Thirty days after the rendition of the judgment or ruling from which the appeal is taken.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="CCRP-914__subsec_B__subsec_2">
            <num>(2)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Thirty days from the ruling on a motion to reconsider sentence filed pursuant to Article 881.1, should such a motion be filed.
Amended by</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=112920</p>
        </authorialNote>
